#: web/views/arenasmith.py:17
msgid "What is Arenasmith?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:19
msgid "Arenasmith is a draft assistant for Hearthstone Arena and Underground Arena, built by the team behind HSReplay.net and Hearthstone Deck Tracker."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:25
msgid "What does Arenasmith do?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:27
msgid "Heroes and cards you are offered in a draft are automatically rated by Arenasmith based on their past in-game performance and your existing picks. It also shows card synergies, what other cards might be generated, and other helpful information."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:34
msgid "How does Arenasmith calculate card ratings?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:36
msgid "The card ratings are calculated across hundreds of thousands of matches from other players, and then dynamically adjusted based on the cards you have already drafted. For example, if you have already picked cards that synergize well with an offered card, Arenasmith will show a better card rating than usual for that card."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:44
msgid "How do I access Arenasmith?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:46
msgid "Arenasmith is a Premium feature available in Hearthstone Deck Tracker. It will automatically appear on the Arena or Underground Arena screen before you start a new draft."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:52
msgid "Do I need to pay to use Arenasmith?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:54
msgid "As a subscriber to our Premium or Bundle subscription, you can use Arenasmith as often as you want in your drafts."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:58
msgid "As a free user, you can trial Arenasmith for ten drafts, and then one draft that resets each week. You can see how many Arenasmith trials you have remaining on the Arena screen in Hearthstone."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:64
msgid "Is Arenasmith available for both The Arena and Underground Arena?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:66
msgid "Yes! Arenasmith is available for all Arena drafts. As a free user, your number of trial drafts is shared across the two game modes."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:71
msgid "How do I know if the Card Ratings are available for Arenasmith?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:73
msgid "Arenasmith is usually available. If it isn't, there will be a message on the Arena screen in Hearthstone before you start a draft. If you decide to proceed anyway and are a free user, this will not use one of your free drafts."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:81
msgid "How long after an expansion or Arena pool update do the Card Ratings update?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:85
msgid "We're currently targeting ~24 hours to collect enough data to power new card ratings for that season, but this may speed up in future."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:90
msgid "Is Arenasmith available for macOS?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:92
msgid "Currently, Arenasmith is not available for macOS through HSTracker. We are planning on adding support in the future!"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/arenasmith.py:100
msgid "Arenasmith - Draft Assistant for Hearthstone Arena"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:145
msgid "Download Hearthstone Deck Tracker for Battlegrounds"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:162
msgid "Is Hearthstone Deck Tracker free?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:164
msgid "Yes! Hearthstone Deck Tracker is completely free to download and use. Core features like Bob's Buddy, opponent tracking, and minion browser are all included at no cost. Tier7 is an optional premium upgrade for players who want lobby-specific data."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:171
msgid "Is Hearthstone Deck Tracker safe to use? Will I get banned?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:173
msgid "Hearthstone Deck Tracker is fully compliant with Blizzard's policies. It only reads publicly available game log files, it never injects code or modifies the game client. Over 20 million players have used it safely since 2015."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:180
msgid "Do I need an account to use Hearthstone Deck Tracker?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:182
msgid "No account is required! Simply download and install, the overlay will start working automatically when you launch it alongside Hearthstone."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:188
msgid "Can I use it on Mac?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:190
msgid "Yes! HSTracker is our Mac companion app with most of the core features."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:194
msgid "Do I need a powerful gaming PC to run Hearthstone Deck Tracker?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:196
msgid "While Hearthstone Deck Tracker works very well on low-spec devices, it will take advantage of extra performance headroom on a powerful device to significantly speed the simulation of combat odds, especially on complex boards, all while carefully avoiding impacting your gaming performance."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:203
msgid "How does Bob's Buddy work?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:205
msgid "Bob's Buddy reads the board state when a combat starts, then it simulates over 10,000 random combat outcomes to calculate your exact win, loss, and tie percentages, including lethal and elimination odds!"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:211
msgid "What is Tier7?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:213
msgid "Tier7 is a set of highly advanced features that add real-time, lobby-specific data to your overlay, including hero tier lists tailored to your lobby's tribes, filtered and tiered composition guides, and tribe performance stats. You automatically get access to it twice a week by using Hearthstone Deck Tracker, and can subscribe for more."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:222 web/views/battlegrounds.py:379
msgid "How often is the data updated?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:224
msgid "Our meta statistics update every hour with the latest games. New patch data is typically available within 2 hours of release, so you always have current information."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:253
msgid "Battleground Stats & Guides"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:255
msgid "Master Hearthstone Battlegrounds with data-driven insights. Explore hero tier lists, winning compositions, minion stats, and more!"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:333
msgid "Level up your gameplay with Tier7's in-depth Battlegrounds statsistics, including actionable information about the best heroes, compositions, minions, and more!"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:344
msgid "Tier7"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:355
msgid "Do I need to pay for Tier7?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:357
msgid "No, all in-game Tier7 features are available for free twice a week by playing with Hearthstone Deck Tracker. If you need more, you can subscribe."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:363
msgid "Can I cancel anytime?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:365
msgid "Yes! You can cancel your subscription at any time from your account settings. You'll continue to have access until the end of your billing period."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:371
msgid "Do I need the Hearthstone Deck Tracker for web features?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:373
msgid "No, the web features (stats, personal dashboard) work independently. However, the Deck Tracker is required for in-game overlays like hero picking and composition stats."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:381
msgid "Our meta statistics update every hour with the latest games. New patch data is typically available within 2 hours of release."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:386
msgid "What MMR bracket should I be to benefit?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:388
msgid "Tier7 helps players at all skill levels. Whether you're climbing from 2k or pushing for top 200, our data ensures you get relevant information for you."
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:394
msgid "Is my account data secure?"
msgstr ""

#: web/views/battlegrounds.py:396
msgid "Absolutely. We use industry-standard encryption and never share your personal information. Your gameplay data is anonymized in our aggregated statistics."
msgstr ""

